cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is about image inpainting, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper proposes a new framework for image inpainting using generative adversarial networks, which involves training a generator and a discriminator to fill in missing regions of an image. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a correlation loss to capture non-local correlations between different patches, which could be relevant to the cs.GR (Graphics) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on three widely-used datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
